When a user runs the Build action (or "Build 390 Stored Procedure"in earlier versions) from
the Data Project Explorer, the build utility is invoked on the remote system and builds the
executable form of the stored procedure. This process includes the compilation of the
source code, the linkage of the load module, the binding of the DB2?package, and what
else?
A. validation of the load module built
B. dropping of stored procedure if one with the same name already exist
C. registration of the stored procedure in the DB2 catalog
D. running of the stored procedure upon a successful build
Answer: C
